Any GDPR Art. 9 special category data tied to an identifiable individual:

- Racial or ethnic origin
- Political opinions
- Religious or philosophical beliefs
- Trade union membership
- Genetic data
- Biometric data used to identify a person (e.g. fingerprints, facial recognition references)
- Health and medical information (diagnoses, treatments, conditions, disabilities)
- Data concerning sex life or sexual orientation

## What is NOT considered sensitive

- Company names, organization names, product names, and publicly available business information
- Public figures referenced in their professional capacity (e.g. CEO statements, politician quotes on policy)
- Aggregated or anonymized statistics that cannot identify individuals
- General personal data already publicly available on the web (names, contact details, etc.)
